{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-10",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_10_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "10 - The Lobster Quadrille",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.759,
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 4,
  "page_start_sec": 250.4,
  "page_end_sec": 494.56,
  "corrected": "claude",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 250.4,
      "end": 251.84,
      "text": "There is another shore,"
    },
    {
      "start": 252.18,
      "end": 252.62,
      "text": "you know,"
    },
    {
      "start": 252.78,
      "end": 254.5,
      "text": "upon the other side."
    },
    {
      "start": 255.22,
      "end": 258.86,
      "text": "The further off from England the nearer is to France--"
    },
    {
      "start": 259.616,
      "end": 260.76,
      "text": "Then turn not pale,"
    },
    {
      "start": 260.92,
      "end": 261.86,
      "text": "beloved snail,"
    },
    {
      "start": 262.14,
      "end": 264.02,
      "text": "but come and join the dance."
    },
    {
      "start": 264.928,
      "end": 265.36,
      "text": "Will you,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 265.44,
      "end": 266.06,
      "text": "won't you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 266.14,
      "end": 266.66,
      "text": "will you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 266.72,
      "end": 267.28,
      "text": "won't you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 267.36,
      "end": 269.0,
      "text": "will you join the dance?"
    },
    {
      "start": 269.856,
      "end": 270.26,
      "text": "Will you,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 270.32,
      "end": 270.9,
      "text": "won't you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 270.98,
      "end": 271.56,
      "text": "will you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 271.6,
      "end": 272.28,
      "text": "won't you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 272.36,
      "end": 274.08,
      "text": "won't you join the dance?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 275.72,
      "end": 276.16,
      "text": "\"Thank you,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 276.3,
      "end": 278.36,
      "text": "it's a very interesting dance to watch,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 278.64,
      "end": 279.54,
      "text": "said Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 279.68,
      "end": 281.9,
      "text": "feeling very glad that it was over at last:"
    },
    {
      "start": 282.66,
      "end": 285.6,
      "text": "\"and I do so like that curious song about the whiting!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 286.58,
      "end": 286.82,
      "text": "\"Oh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 286.98,
      "end": 288.36,
      "text": "as to the whiting,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 288.62,
      "end": 289.64,
      "text": "said the Mock Turtle,"
    },
    {
      "start": 290.28,
      "end": 290.44,
      "text": "\"they--"
    },
    {
      "start": 290.76,
      "end": 291.82,
      "text": "you've seen them,"
    },
    {
      "start": 291.88,
      "end": 292.4,
      "text": "of course?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 293.42,
      "end": 293.94,
      "text": "\"Yes,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 294.16,
      "end": 294.72,
      "text": "said Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 294.9,
      "end": 296.64,
      "text": "\"I've often seen them at dinn----\""
    },
    {
      "start": 297.3,
      "end": 298.48,
      "text": "she checked herself hastily."
    },
    {
      "start": 299.96,
      "end": 302.1,
      "text": "\"I don't know where Dinn may be,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 302.37,
      "end": 303.34,
      "text": "said the Mock Turtle,"
    },
    {
      "start": 304.22,
      "end": 306.32,
      "text": "\"but if you've seen them so often,"
    },
    {
      "start": 306.54,
      "end": 308.7,
      "text": "of course you know what they're like.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 309.58,
      "end": 310.36,
      "text": "\"I believe so,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 310.7,
      "end": 312.1,
      "text": "Alice replied thoughtfully."
    },
    {
      "start": 312.54,
      "end": 314.24,
      "text": "\"They have their tails in their mouths--"
    },
    {
      "start": 314.34,
      "end": 315.44,
      "text": "and they're all over crumbs.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 316.864,
      "end": 318.44,
      "text": "\"You're wrong about the crumbs,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 318.82,
      "end": 319.78,
      "text": "said the Mock Turtle:"
    },
    {
      "start": 320.416,
      "end": 322.36,
      "text": "\"crumbs would all wash off in the sea."
    },
    {
      "start": 323.04,
      "end": 325.08,
      "text": "But they _have_ their tails in their mouths;"
    },
    {
      "start": 325.984,
      "end": 327.808,
      "text": "and the reason is--\""
    },
    {
      "start": 328.38,
      "end": 330.48,
      "text": "here the Mock Turtle yawned and shut his eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 331.4,
      "end": 335.18,
      "text": "\"Tell her about the reason and all that,\" he said to the Gryphon.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 336.06,
      "end": 337.84,
      "text": "\"The reason is,\" said the Gryphon,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 338.3,
      "end": 340.46,
      "text": "\"that they _would_ go with the lobsters to the dance,"
    },
    {
      "start": 340.64,
      "end": 342.1,
      "text": "so they got thrown out to sea."
    },
    {
      "start": 342.7,
      "end": 344.22,
      "text": "So they had to fall a long way."
    },
    {
      "start": 344.72,
      "end": 346.56,
      "text": "So they got their tails fast in their mouths."
    },
    {
      "start": 346.96,
      "end": 348.16,
      "text": "So they couldn't get them out again."
    },
    {
      "start": 349.024,
      "end": 349.472,
      "text": "That's all.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 351.136,
      "end": 352.36,
      "text": "\"Thank you,\" said Alice.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 352.62,
      "end": 353.6,
      "text": "\"It's very interesting."
    },
    {
      "start": 354.34,
      "end": 356.6,
      "text": "I never knew so much about a whiting before.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 358.14,
      "end": 359.98,
      "text": "\"I can tell you more than that, if you like,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 360.16,
      "end": 360.7,
      "text": "said the Gryphon."
    },
    {
      "start": 360.78,
      "end": 362.14,
      "text": "\"Do you know why it's called"
    },
    {
      "start": 362.26,
      "end": 362.56,
      "text": "a whiting?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 363.53,
      "end": 365.08,
      "text": "\"I never thought about it,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 365.18,
      "end": 365.6,
      "text": "said Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 365.8,
      "end": 366.16,
      "text": "\"Why?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 368.24,
      "end": 369.44,
      "text": "\"_It does the boots and shoes_,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 369.84,
      "end": 371.89,
      "text": "the Gryphon replied very solemnly."
    },
    {
      "start": 372.8,
      "end": 374.2,
      "text": "Alice was thoroughly puzzled.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 374.94,
      "end": 376.16,
      "text": "\"Does the boots and shoes!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 376.5,
      "end": 378.22,
      "text": "she repeated in a wondering tone."
    },
    {
      "start": 378.94,
      "end": 379.12,
      "text": "\"Why,"
    },
    {
      "start": 379.26,
      "end": 380.58,
      "text": "what are _your_ shoes done with?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 380.72,
      "end": 381.58,
      "text": "said the Gryphon."
    },
    {
      "start": 381.62,
      "end": 382.02,
      "text": "\"I mean,"
    },
    {
      "start": 382.02,
      "end": 383.06,
      "text": "what makes them so shiny?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 384.32,
      "end": 386.04,
      "text": "Alice looked down at them, and considered",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 386.04,
      "end": 387.74,
      "text": "a little before she gave her answer."
    },
    {
      "start": 388.8,
      "end": 389.8,
      "text": "\"They're done with blacking,"
    },
    {
      "start": 389.8,
      "end": 390.16,
      "text": "I believe.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 391.584,
      "end": 393.0,
      "text": "\"Boots and shoes under the sea,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 393.22,
      "end": 394.98,
      "text": "the Gryphon went on in a deep voice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 395.34,
      "end": 396.32,
      "text": "\"are done with whiting."
    },
    {
      "start": 396.52,
      "end": 397.28,
      "text": "Now you know.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 398.28,
      "end": 399.2,
      "text": "\"And what are they made of?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 399.38,
      "end": 401.5,
      "text": "Alice asked in a tone of great curiosity."
    },
    {
      "start": 402.816,
      "end": 403.52,
      "text": "\"Soles and eels,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 403.56,
      "end": 404.0,
      "text": "of course,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 404.14,
      "end": 406.28,
      "text": "the Gryphon replied rather impatiently:"
    },
    {
      "start": 406.86,
      "end": 408.14,
      "text": "\"any shrimp could have told you that.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 409.3,
      "end": 410.42,
      "text": "\"If I'd been the whiting,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 410.58,
      "end": 411.16,
      "text": "said Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 411.32,
      "end": 413.04,
      "text": "whose thoughts were still running on the song,"
    },
    {
      "start": 413.64,
      "end": 414.73,
      "text": "\"I'd have said to the porpoise,"
    },
    {
      "start": 414.92,
      "end": 415.48,
      "text": "'Keep back,"
    },
    {
      "start": 415.54,
      "end": 415.78,
      "text": "please:"
    },
    {
      "start": 415.92,
      "end": 417.02,
      "text": "we don't want _you_ with us!'\""
    },
    {
      "start": 419.22,
      "end": 422.98,
      "text": "\"They were obliged to have him with them,\" the Mock Turtle said:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 423.78,
      "end": 427.32,
      "text": "\"no wise fish would go anywhere without a porpoise.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 428.832,
      "end": 431.64,
      "text": "\"Wouldn't it really?\" said Alice in a tone of great surprise.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 433.376,
      "end": 435.48,
      "text": "\"Of course not,\" said the Mock Turtle:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 435.98,
      "end": 436.32,
      "text": "\"why,"
    },
    {
      "start": 436.44,
      "end": 440.98,
      "text": "if a fish came to _me_, and told me he was going a journey,"
    },
    {
      "start": 441.2,
      "end": 442.18,
      "text": "I should say,"
    },
    {
      "start": 442.4,
      "end": 444.22,
      "text": "'With what porpoise?'\""
    },
    {
      "start": 445.28,
      "end": 447.0,
      "text": "\"Don't you mean 'purpose'?\" said Alice.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 447.2,
      "end": 449.12,
      "text": "\"I mean what I say,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 449.48,
      "end": 451.9,
      "text": "the Mock Turtle replied in an offended tone."
    },
    {
      "start": 452.64,
      "end": 453.48,
      "text": "And the Gryphon added,"
    },
    {
      "start": 454.08,
      "end": 454.42,
      "text": "\"Come,"
    },
    {
      "start": 454.62,
      "end": 455.74,
      "text": "let's hear some of _your_ adventures.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 456.52,
      "end": 458.0,
      "text": "\"I could tell you my adventures--",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 458.3,
      "end": 459.76,
      "text": "beginning from this morning,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 460.08,
      "end": 461.68,
      "text": "said Alice a little timidly:"
    },
    {
      "start": 462.34,
      "end": 464.16,
      "text": "\"but it's no use going back to yesterday,"
    },
    {
      "start": 464.42,
      "end": 466.12,
      "text": "because I was a different person then.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 467.424,
      "end": 468.6,
      "text": "\"Explain all that,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 469.02,
      "end": 470.18,
      "text": "said the Mock Turtle."
    },
    {
      "start": 471.06,
      "end": 471.24,
      "text": "\"No,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 471.32,
      "end": 471.54,
      "text": "no!"
    },
    {
      "start": 471.58,
      "end": 472.42,
      "text": "The adventures first,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 472.72,
      "end": 474.78,
      "text": "said the Gryphon in an impatient tone:"
    },
    {
      "start": 475.264,
      "end": 476.96,
      "text": "\"explanations take such a dreadful time.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 478.88,
      "end": 481.54,
      "text": "So Alice began telling them her adventures from",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 481.54,
      "end": 483.74,
      "text": "the time when she first saw the White Rabbit."
    },
    {
      "start": 484.24,
      "end": 486.44,
      "text": "She was a little nervous about it just at first,"
    },
    {
      "start": 486.74,
      "end": 488.36,
      "text": "the two creatures got so close to her,"
    },
    {
      "start": 488.42,
      "end": 489.34,
      "text": "one on each side,"
    },
    {
      "start": 489.7,
      "end": 492.38,
      "text": "and opened their eyes and mouths so _very_ wide,"
    },
    {
      "start": 492.52,
      "end": 494.56,
      "text": "but she gained courage as she went on."
    }
  ]
}